Introduction- Pro Kabbadi League¶

Pro Kabaddi League-Introduction Kabaddi is an Indian contact team sport.Played between two teams of seven players, the objective of the game is for a single player on offence, referred to as a "raider", to run into the opposing team's half of a court, touch out as many of their defenders as possible, and return to their own half of the court, all without being tackled by the defenders, and in a single breath.Points are scored for each player tagged by the raider, while the opposing team earns a point for stopping the raider. Players are taken out of the game if they are touched or tackled, but are brought back in for each point scored by their team from a tag or tackle.

Plot 8 describes how many players got points by Super Tackles

Tackling a raider and stopping him from escaping to the midline amounts to one point in kabaddi, however, if a team is reduced to three or fewer players, executing the same earns them an extra point, therefore a total of two points for a single tackle. Such a tackle is known as a ‘Super Tackle’.¶

Super Tackles by Bengal Warriors¶

Super 10s by Bengal Warriors¶

A Super 10 is achieved when a raider scores 10 or more raid points in a single game. The points could be either bonus or touch points but not points awarded to the overall team, such as technical points. A raider needs to be agile and quick thinker to be aware of the opportunities available to pick up points by exploiting the chinks in the opposition defence. He also needs to have multiple attacking options at his disposal if he hopes to outfox the opposition defence repeatedly and return with 10 or more raid points.

Super Raids by Bengal Warriors¶
